  "prompt": "My pet cat scratched me accidentally.Its not vaccinated and I'm from India. 7 days have passed but the cat is fully well. Do I need anti-rabies shots?",
  "response": "In India, if you are scratched by a cat, even if it appears healthy, it\u2019s important to consider the possibility of rabies, especially if the cat is unvaccinated. The rabies virus can be present even in seemingly healthy animals.\n\nYou should consult a healthcare professional as soon as possible for an assessment. They might recommend post-exposure prophylaxis (PEP) depending on the risk factors and the circumstances of the scratch. Since 7 days have already passed, it\u2019s crucial to seek medical advice promptly to discuss whether you need the rabies vaccination or other treatments.",
